cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.CE, cs.DB

The paper proposes a novel framework based on deep learning for identifying higher-order SNP interactions in GWAS data to classify preterm births. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the paper uses deep learning and classification tasks. Additionally, cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology) is also a likely sub-category as the paper focuses on a complex medical condition with a strong genetic component. Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses a GWAS data set obtained from dbGap.
